## 7. Import Path: Community Skills → Brain Graph

Issue #177 specifies compatibility with the 80k+ skills.sh ecosystem. With this integration:

### Inbound: skills.sh → Brain

```typescript
// Import flow
// 1. Admin installs a skill from skills.sh
const skillConfig = { type: "github", source: "anthropics/skills", skills: ["code-review"] };

// 2. Brain fetches SKILL.md, parses frontmatter
const parsed = parseSkillMd(content);

// 3. Creates graph node
await query(`CREATE skill CONTENT $content`, {
  content: {
    name: parsed.name,
    description: parsed.description,
    content: parsed.body,
    triggers: extractTriggers(parsed.description),
    version: parsed.metadata?.version ?? "1.0",
    status: "draft",  // Human reviews before activation
    workspace: workspaceRecord,
  }
});

// 4. LLM analyzes tool requirements → creates skill_requires edges
await analyzeToolRequirements(skill, workspaceTools);
```

### Outbound: Brain Skill → Sandbox Agent session

The materialization flow in Section 5 handles this. Brain skills become `SKILL.md` files that any Agent Skills-compatible sandbox agent can discover.

### Round-trip: skills.sh → Brain → SKILL.md → sandbox agent

```
skills.sh registry
  ↓ import (parse SKILL.md frontmatter)
Brain SurrealDB (skill table)
  ↓ materialize (generate SKILL.md)
/tmp/brain-skills/{session}/{name}/SKILL.md
  ↓ setSkillsConfig (register with sandbox agent)
Sandbox Agent session
  ↓ native discovery (Agent Skills spec)
Agent activates skill based on task context
  ↓ tool calls flow through Brain MCP
Brain enforces governance (intent auth + policy)
```

